cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the control of a network of signalized intersections, which can be considered a type of network architecture. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a control algorithm for the queuing network, which falls under the category of systems and control. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses simulation results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which can be considered a type of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for traffic signal control, which can be considered a type of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper mentions the ability of the proposed algorithm to be distributed over intersections, which falls under the category of distributed computing.
